  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bulma@0.9.4/css/bulma.min.css">
</head>
<body>
  <nav class="navbar is-primary" role="navigation">
    <div class="navbar-brand">
      <a class="navbar-item" href="/">
        <strong>üìä SQLite Demo</strong>
      </a>
    </div>
    <div class="navbar-menu">
      <div class="navbar-start">
        <a class="navbar-item" href="/">Students</a>
        <a class="navbar-item" href="/about">About</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="title">‚ÑπÔ∏è About This App</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">SQLite Database Information</p>

      <div class="box">
        <h2 class="title is-4">Database Details</h2>
        
        <div class="content">
          <p><strong>Database Path:</strong></p>
          <pre><code><%= dbPath %></code></pre>

          <p><strong>Total Records:</strong> <%= rowCount %> students</p>

          <p><strong>Table Name:</strong> <%= tableInfo.name %></p>

          <p><strong>Table Schema:</strong></p>
          <pre><code><%= tableInfo.sql %></code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="box">
        <h2 class="title is-4">Why SQLite?</h2>
        <div class="content">
          <h3>Advantages over JSON files:</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Speed:</strong> Much faster for large datasets</li>
            <li><strong>Queries:</strong> Powerful SQL for filtering, sorting, joining</li>
            <li><strong>Relationships:</strong> Link tables together (foreign keys)</li>
            <li><strong>Transactions:</strong> Safe concurrent writes</li>
            <li><strong>Data Integrity:</strong> Enforce rules (unique, not null, etc.)</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>When to use JSON vs Database:</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>JSON:</strong> Small datasets (&lt;100 items), simple structure, learning</li>
            <li><strong>Database:</strong> Large datasets, complex queries, production apps</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="notification is-warning">
        <p class="heading">‚ö†Ô∏è Important for Railway Deployment</p>
        <p>This app uses Railway volumes for persistent storage. Without volumes, the database resets on each deployment.</p>
        <p>For local development, data persists in <code>students.db</code> file.</p>
      </div>

      <a href="/" class="button is-primary">‚Üê Back to Student List</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</body>
</html>
